Alternative forms[edit]

  • imperō

Etymology[edit]

From indu- +‎ parō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /inˈdu.pe.roː/, [ɪn̪ˈd̪ʊ.pɛ.roː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /inˈdu.pe.ro/, [in̪ˈd̪uː.pɛ.rɔ]

Verb[edit]

induperō (present infinitive induperāre, perfect active induperāvī, supine induperātum); first conjugation

  1. (with dative) (archaic) I command, give orders to
